<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="457" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,150,1257]" pageId="28" pageNumber="457">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,655,681]" pageId="28" pageNumber="457">Etymology.</emphasis>
This new species is named for my recently deceased (2011) colleague, Alexander “Al” A. Hubert, former Lt. Colonel with 
<collectingCountry box="[426,482,691,717]" name="United States of America" pageId="28" pageNumber="457">U. S.</collectingCountry>
Army Walter Reed Institute of Research, 
<collectingRegion box="[951,1087,691,717]" country="United States of America" name="Washington" pageId="28" pageNumber="457">Washington</collectingRegion>
, D. C., who collected the 
<typeStatus pageId="28" pageNumber="457">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus box="[255,345,727,753]" pageId="28" pageNumber="457">allotype</typeStatus>
and in recognition of his important contributions to the systematics of ceratopogonids. His large book “The 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1809" box="[275,395,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Culicoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="457" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[275,395,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="457">Culicoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of Southeast Asia”, that he coauthored with Willis W. Wirth (
<bibRefCitation author="Wirth, W. W. &amp; Hubert, A. A." box="[1072,1312,763,789]" pageId="28" pageNumber="457" pagination="1 - 508" refId="ref33293" refString="Wirth, W. W. &amp; Hubert, A. A. (1989) The Culicoides of Southeast Asia (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae). Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 44, 1 - 508." type="journal article" year="1989">Wirth &amp; Hubert 1989</bibRefCitation>
) dealt with 168 species, of which 53 were new species. Al was also a co-author with Wirth on seven other articles on biting and predaceous midges, and he has four other prior ceratopogonid patronyms: 
<taxonomicName authority="Wirth &amp; Delfinado (1964)" authorityName="Wirth &amp; Delfinado" authorityYear="1964" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Alluaudomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="457" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huberti">
<emphasis box="[976,1220,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="457">Alluaudomyia huberti</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wirth, W. W. &amp; Delfinado, M. D." pageId="28" pageNumber="457" pagination="599 - 848" refId="ref33160" refString="Wirth, W. W. &amp; Delfinado, M. D. (1964) Revision of the oriental species of Alluaudomyia Kieffer (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae). Pacific Insects, 6, 599 - 848." type="journal article" year="1964">Wirth &amp; Delfinado (1964)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Das Gupta &amp; Wirth (1968)" authorityName="Das Gupta &amp; Wirth" authorityYear="1968" box="[239,754,871,898]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Stilobezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="457" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huberti">
<emphasis box="[239,448,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="457">Stilobezzia huberti</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Das Gupta, S. K. &amp; Wirth, W. W." box="[454,754,871,898]" pageId="28" pageNumber="457" pagination="1 - 149" refId="ref31159" refString="Das Gupta, S. K. &amp; Wirth, W. W. (1968) Revision of the Oriental species of Stilobezzia Kieffer midges (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae). United States National Museum Bulletin, 283, 1 - 149. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 03629236.283.1" type="journal article" year="1968">Das Gupta &amp; Wirth (1968)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Grogan &amp; Wirth (1977)" authorityName="Grogan &amp; Wirth" authorityYear="1977" box="[766,1251,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Parabezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="457" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huberti">
<emphasis box="[766,979,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="457">Parabezzia huberti</emphasis>
Grogan &amp; Wirth (1977)
</taxonomicName>
, and, 
<taxonomicName authority="Howarth (1985)" authorityName="Howarth" authorityYear="1985" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Culicoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="457" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huberti">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="457">Culicoides huberti</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Howarth, F. G." box="[239,422,906,933]" pageId="28" pageNumber="457" pagination="1 - 96" refId="ref31748" refString="Howarth, F. G. (1985) Biosystematics of the Culicoides of Laos (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae). International Journal of Entomology, 27, 1 - 96." type="journal article" year="1985">Howarth (1985)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
