<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="457" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,150,1257]" pageId="28" pageNumber="457">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1158,1184]" pageId="28" pageNumber="457">Discussion.</emphasis>
Both sexes of four other species in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Coquillett" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[767,895,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="457" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulverea">
<emphasis box="[767,784,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="457">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[798,895,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="457">pulverea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Coquillett" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[1010,1138,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="457" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulverea">
<emphasis box="[1010,1027,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="457">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1041,1138,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="457">pulverea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1151,1232,1159,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="457" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spicata">
<emphasis box="[1151,1232,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="457">spicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Grogan, 2020" authorityName="Grogan" authorityYear="2020" box="[1245,1371,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="457" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="titanochela" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1245,1371,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="457">titanochela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1377,1436,1159,1185]" pageId="28" pageNumber="457" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and males of 
<taxonomicName authority="Grogan, 2020" authorityName="Grogan" authorityYear="2020" box="[297,436,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="457" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leptostyla" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[297,314,1195,1220]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="457">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[327,436,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="457">leptostyla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[442,501,1195,1221]" pageId="28" pageNumber="457" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(females unknown), also have hind tibiae with pale subapical bands. However, these species differ from this new species by the characters provided in the key, their diagnoses and descriptions.
</paragraph>
